SYMPTOM

User reported that their laptop would not charge. They tested multiple power outlets but the battery continued to drain and the device would not charge.

ISOLATION

Troubleshooting performed:

Verified the user tried multiple wall outlets.
Confirmed the charging cable was securely connected.
Suspected the charger was faulty based on the initial symptoms.
Sent a replacement charger to restore service as quickly as possible.
After the replacement charger arrived, the issue persisted, confirming the charger was not the cause.
ROOT CAUSE

The laptop itself had a hardware fault preventing it from accepting a charge. The charging circuit or another internal hardware component had failed, rather than the power adapter.

FIX
Initially arranged shipment of a replacement charger based on the reported symptoms.
After confirming the new charger did not resolve the issue, prepared a replacement work laptop using the appropriate company image.
Registered the new asset, assigned it to the user, and shipped it with expedited delivery.
Included a return label for the defective laptop so it could be returned for hardware diagnostics.
VERIFICATION

User received the replacement laptop, successfully signed in, confirmed the device charged normally, and resumed work without further issues.

PREVENTION
Verify suspected charger failures by testing with a known-good charger before replacing accessories.
Keep pre-imaged replacement laptops available for users who rely on their devices for business-critical work.
Encourage users to report intermittent charging issues before complete hardware failure occurs.
